    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Missile Shield: A National Priority?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Olivia Kienzel letter endorses Richard Perle's July 13 Op-Ed article arguing case for national missile defense system</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Better Way to Build a Missile Defense,'' by Richard Perle (Op-Ed,  July 13): I was glad to read a new perspective on the missile defense issue. Why does it seem as if the burden of preventing arms proliferation is placed on the defender instead of on the aggressor? It's like telling someone to stop dodging so you can hit him harder.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Better Way to Build a Missile Defense,'' by Richard Perle (Op-Ed,  July 13): I was glad to read a new perspective on the missile defense issue. Why does it seem as if the burden of preventing arms proliferation is placed on the defender instead of on the aggressor? It's like telling someone to stop dodging so you can hit him harder.</p>
        <p>The nuclear proliferation of other countries is quite obviously out of our hands, and such an unpredictable climate would seem to require that we develop as sophisticated a way of protecting ourselves as possible.</p>
        <p>OLIVIA KIENZEL  Carpinteria, Calif., July 13, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
